Which of the following commands shows network services or sockets that are currentlylistening along with sockets that are not listening?
A)  netstat - a
B)  netlink - a
C)  sockets - f
D)  opensock - l
A
A. The netstat command is used for this purpose, and the - a option displays all sockets,listening and non- listening. Note that its frequently helpful to add the - n option, or com-bine them as in netstat an, in order to prevent name lookup. Doing so can significantlyimprove performance of the command.
